<quiz>
    <question>
        <prompt>The Hays Code was significant in the 1920s because it:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Regulated railroad safety standards</option>
            <option letter="b">Established moral guidelines for motion pictures</option>
            <option letter="c">Created banking regulations</option>
            <option letter="d">Set immigration quotas</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Hays Code, formally adopted in 1930 but developed in the 1920s, was a set of moral guidelines for motion pictures. Named after Will Hays, it regulated film content by prohibiting certain themes, behaviors, and images deemed morally inappropriate. This self-imposed censorship by the film industry was a response to public concerns about Hollywood's influence on social values.</explanation>
    </question>
</quiz>
